title: Refactor skills to work like Claude Code's skills
---
Refactor clawq skills to follow Claude Code's skill model for richer structure and better agent integration.

## Current clawq model
- JSON files with shell command templates
- Direct execution, stdout returned to agent
- Each skill appears as a separate tool

## Proposed Claude Code-style model
- SKILL.md with YAML frontmatter + markdown instructions
- Supporting files: scripts, templates, examples, references
- Single Skill tool that loads skill instructions on-demand
- Frontmatter metadata: allowed-tools, context, agent settings

## Benefits
- Richer structure (supporting files, examples, templates)
- Better separation: instructions vs execution
- More portable between agent implementations
- Frontmatter control over tool access, model invocation, etc.

## Migration path
1. Support both formats during transition
2. Convert existing skills (review-and-fix, watch_ci_after_push)
3. Update skill_list, skill_create tools
4. Document new format in skills docs